1
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:47,710
You alive in there?

2
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:50,349
Yeah.

3
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:54,115
You're 15 minutes late, Lefty.

4
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:55,778
Dale's looking for you,

5
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:57,857
and he's more pissed than usual.

6
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:02,520
- You hear what I said?
- Yeah. I'm coming.

7
00:01:05,832 --> 00:01:07,197
- Hey.
- What?

8
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:11,196
Thanks for making me late.

9
00:01:11,304 --> 00:01:13,898
Gee, I'm sorry.
My boss, who pays me,

10
00:01:14,007 --> 00:01:15,304
wanted me to do something.

11
00:01:15,408 --> 00:01:17,706
Next time I'll tell him I work for Lefty.

12
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,907
Hey, princess.

13
00:01:56,015 --> 00:01:57,277
When you're done putting your makeup on,

14
00:01:57,383 --> 00:01:59,408
get your royal behind in my office.

15
00:03:15,528 --> 00:03:18,326
Say, Dale, I'm gonna need
an extended lunch today,

16
00:03:18,431 --> 00:03:22,094
seeing as I got a meeting
with my wife's lawyers.

17
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:23,669
You must be joking.

18
00:03:24,837 --> 00:03:26,270
No, Dale, I'm not.

19
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:27,532
Now, I know that you're...

20
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:29,801
Come on, Lefty.
What's wrong with you?

21
00:03:29,909 --> 00:03:33,401
Am I nuts, or did we have
a conversation yesterday?

22
00:03:33,513 --> 00:03:36,448
What wasn't clear about what I said, Lefty?

23
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:39,609
Didn't I warn you
that was the last time?

24
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,209
We talked about it.

25
00:03:41,321 --> 00:03:43,289
What else can I do for you?

26
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:45,050
I got you the promotion.

27
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:47,888
Nobody else thought it was a good idea,
but I pushed it,

28
00:03:47,994 --> 00:03:50,258
and you thank me
by being late every day since.

29
00:03:50,363 --> 00:03:52,593
Every day. How is that possible?

30
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:56,834
You think this is funny?

31
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:00,630
I can't believe I wasted my time on you.

32
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:02,503
Look, Dale...

33
00:04:02,609 --> 00:04:04,133
I appreciate the promotion.

34
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:05,643
I do.

35
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:07,042
But you gotta understand.

36
00:04:07,146 --> 00:04:08,807
Now that I'm making more money,

37
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:12,646
I'll admit I've been partying a little bit more.

38
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,811
But that will not...

39
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:16,388
affect my work.

40
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,885
Please tell me you're not that stupid.

41
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:23,320
I gave you a promotion.
You didn't get a raise.

42
00:04:24,364 --> 00:04:27,492
Assistant Production Line
Supervisor?

43
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,897
It doesn't mean a thing.

44
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:30,333
It's just a name.

45
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:33,234
I did it for your custody case

46
00:04:33,339 --> 00:04:35,705
because I knew it'd look good
for the judge and your kids.

47
00:04:35,808 --> 00:04:38,436
But you... you take that...
that... that charity,

48
00:04:38,544 --> 00:04:40,671
and you blow it up in my face.

49
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:43,248
I'm not blind. I know you're drinking again.

50
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,179
You're hopeless, Lefty.

51
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,914
Sucks to hear it, I know,
but somebody needs to tell you.

52
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:51,916
I'm sorry, man.

53
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,085
I gotta do it.

54
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:58,389
Now, Dale, before you go
and do something stupid,

55
00:04:58,498 --> 00:05:00,193
you really ought to think about it.

56
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:04,464
I mean, this place would
shut down without me.

57
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,730
Who else is gonna go out there

58
00:05:05,838 --> 00:05:08,102
and change all those belts on the line?

59
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:12,611
Anyone with opposable thumbs.

60
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:18,211
Playtime's over.
Clear out your locker and go home.

61
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:20,218
You're fired.

62
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,447
An escort will walk you to your car.

63
00:05:24,023 --> 00:05:24,955
Now, Dale...

64
00:05:25,058 --> 00:05:26,116
Go home, Lefty.

65
00:06:34,694 --> 00:06:36,594
Hi, Jacob.
How you doing, buddy?

66
00:06:36,696 --> 00:06:37,958
Hi, Mary.

67
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:39,588
- You doing okay?
- Fine, thanks.

68
00:06:39,699 --> 00:06:41,462
- You?
- Seriously.

69
00:06:42,502 --> 00:06:43,969
You doing all right?

70
00:06:45,571 --> 00:06:47,300
As good as can be expected.

71
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:48,874
Seriously.

72
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:54,743
I love you, Jacob. You be good.

73
00:06:54,847 --> 00:06:55,836
Love you.

74
00:06:55,948 --> 00:06:57,609
His juice box is in his backpack.

75
00:06:57,717 --> 00:06:59,446
He'll try to tell you
I forgot to give him one...

76
00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:01,110
Got it.

77
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:03,051
Hey, you know
these seats are adjustable.

78
00:07:03,156 --> 00:07:04,145
Oh, yeah.

79
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,122
This is the way Rick liked it, though,

80
00:07:06,225 --> 00:07:09,217
so... I just, um...

81
00:07:09,328 --> 00:07:10,295
you know.

82
00:07:10,396 --> 00:07:11,988
Yeah.

83
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:13,065
Okay.

84
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:17,235
- See you at 3.
- I'll see you at 3. Bye.

85
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,241
Pump one.

86
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:49,867
This plus 20 bucks on 2.

87
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:51,436
21.05.

88
00:08:07,086 --> 00:08:08,053
Problem?

89
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,187
No, it's really good, actually.

90
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:26,865
Where's Security?

91
00:08:26,973 --> 00:08:29,567
The least they could do
is have Security take me out.

92
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:32,235
Security's got sensitivity training today.

93
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:35,075
Yeah, well, this isn't very sensitive.

94
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:36,546
Yes.

95
00:08:36,649 --> 00:08:37,946
Go home, Lefty.

96
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:42,647
It's kinda hard when you're standing
in the middle of my living room.

97
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:45,650
Yes. Good luck, buddy.

98
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:01,039
Hey!

99
00:09:01,140 --> 00:09:02,334
Got a fiver?

100
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,170
Just till payday?

101
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:20,021
I'll show you playtime, Dale.

102
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:31,328
<i>...to consider the feelings of the violator,</i>

103
00:09:31,437 --> 00:09:33,564
<i>at least on par with</i>
<i>those of the violated.</i>

104
00:09:33,673 --> 00:09:35,971
<i>We mustn't forget,</i>
<i>before they were perpetrators,</i>

105
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:37,872
<i>they were victims themselves.</i>

106
00:09:37,977 --> 00:09:39,376
<i>So they are hurting individuals,</i>

107
00:09:39,478 --> 00:09:41,139
<i>deserving of our empathy, concern,</i>

108
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:43,715
<i>and, yes, our love and compassion.</i>

109
00:09:43,816 --> 00:09:45,579
<i>Perhaps you can ask, them, brother...</i>

110
00:09:45,685 --> 00:09:46,811
<i>or sister...</i>

111
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:48,079
<i>if... if they're comfortable with that,</i>

112
00:09:48,187 --> 00:09:49,779
<i>"Why is it that you felt compelled</i>

113
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:51,720
<i>to take what did not belong to you?"</i>

114
00:10:15,548 --> 00:10:16,572
It's prepay only.

115
00:10:16,682 --> 00:10:18,616
I don't care what day it is.

116
00:10:18,718 --> 00:10:21,812
I guess that would explain the sign
right in front of my eyes

117
00:10:21,921 --> 00:10:23,149
that says "Prepay only," huh?

118
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:31,093
It kind of sucks working today, huh?

119
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:32,095
Christmas Eve and all?

120
00:10:33,199 --> 00:10:35,963
Working Christmas Eve. No fun.

121
00:10:36,068 --> 00:10:38,730
Oh. Yeah. I guess.

122
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:40,271
Boss gave you the raw deal.

123
00:10:40,373 --> 00:10:41,567
You're looking at him.

124
00:10:44,276 --> 00:10:45,903
Then why the heck
are you working today?

125
00:10:46,012 --> 00:10:48,845
Kid didn't show up today.
Called in sick this morning.

126
00:10:48,948 --> 00:10:50,506
What else am I going to do?

127
00:10:50,616 --> 00:10:51,981
Kids aren't the most
dependable creatures.

128
00:10:52,084 --> 00:10:53,984
20 bucks on 2.

129
00:10:54,086 --> 00:10:56,350
So you even have
to be open today?

130
00:10:56,455 --> 00:10:57,854
Chug-a-Lug and Neighbor Mart
are closed.

131
00:10:57,957 --> 00:11:00,687
It would be stupid to pass up
the Christmas Eve rush.

132
00:11:01,861 --> 00:11:04,386
Oh. Yeah.

133
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:05,657
27.01.

134
00:11:10,403 --> 00:11:11,961
Thank you.

135
00:11:13,305 --> 00:11:14,397
Merry Christmas.

136
00:11:15,474 --> 00:11:16,839
Yep.

137
00:11:19,111 --> 00:11:20,442
Hello?

138
00:11:20,546 --> 00:11:23,413
Uh, is, uh... I was...

139
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,814
Is this the walk-in clinic?

140
00:11:25,918 --> 00:11:27,385
Oh, good.

141
00:11:27,486 --> 00:11:29,920
I was afraid I had the wrong number
for a minute.

142
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:33,958
Um, um, l... I saw Dr. Lyndel yesterday,

143
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:35,459
and I'm... I'm a little confused

144
00:11:35,561 --> 00:11:37,620
about some of the medications he gave me.

145
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:39,630
I think I need a little help w...

146
00:11:39,732 --> 00:11:42,394
Uh, yeah, I can wait, okay.

147
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:47,197
Uh, hi. This is Eva Boyle.

148
00:11:47,306 --> 00:11:49,934
Yeah, I saw Dr. Lyndel last week,

149
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:53,068
and I was wanting to...

150
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:57,209
I wasn't expecting you, Dr. Lyndel.

151
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,817
What...

152
00:11:59,919 --> 00:12:01,443
No. Uh...

153
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:02,816
I know it was yesterday.

154
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:04,389
I told that woman that.

155
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:06,321
Anyway, I know you told me

156
00:12:06,425 --> 00:12:08,916
to take some medications
in the morning

157
00:12:09,028 --> 00:12:11,826
and some in the afternoon...

158
00:12:11,931 --> 00:12:13,956
I did?

159
00:12:15,835 --> 00:12:18,963
I did. I wrote it down right here.

160
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:22,768
Oh. Now I do feel silly.

161
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:25,673
Well, uh, which...

162
00:12:25,778 --> 00:12:26,710
Uh-huh.

163
00:12:26,812 --> 00:12:28,837
Yeah, the... Oh.

164
00:12:28,948 --> 00:12:30,040
The red with the red

165
00:12:30,149 --> 00:12:31,673
and the yellow with the yellow.

166
00:12:32,785 --> 00:12:34,343
Thank you so much.

167
00:12:34,453 --> 00:12:37,752
L... I know I wasted your time,

168
00:12:37,857 --> 00:12:39,688
but I just remember
your telling me

169
00:12:39,792 --> 00:12:41,123
that I need to be careful

170
00:12:41,227 --> 00:12:44,196
which ones I took
with which and when.

171
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:47,690
Thank you.

172
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,961
Merry Christmas to you, too, Doctor.

173
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:51,468
Thank you.

174
00:13:16,195 --> 00:13:18,561
Ah, Mitch. Putting the music together.

175
00:13:18,664 --> 00:13:20,359
Hey, Pastor Mark.
Yeah, I'm almost done.

176
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:23,401
I put these packets together
for you to give out.

177
00:13:23,502 --> 00:13:26,403
There's a card, a Christmas CD,

178
00:13:26,505 --> 00:13:29,201
and 20 bucks in each one.

179
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:31,208
Isn't this kind of insulting?

180
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:32,641
No. I don't think so.

181
00:13:32,745 --> 00:13:34,440
I want to give them
something they need

182
00:13:34,547 --> 00:13:37,414
rather than some kind of tree ornament
or a candy cane or something.

183
00:13:37,516 --> 00:13:39,984
I'm just not sure
how they're going to take it.

184
00:13:40,085 --> 00:13:43,612
L... I gather you're not,
uh, excited about tonight?

185
00:13:43,722 --> 00:13:45,656
Not tremendously, no.

186
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:47,783
I mean, we're talking about
high school students here.

187
00:13:47,893 --> 00:13:50,623
The last thing they want to do
is go caroling for old people.

188
00:13:50,729 --> 00:13:52,321
I mean, it's not 1948 anymore.

189
00:13:52,431 --> 00:13:53,989
Fair enough, Mitch,

190
00:13:54,099 --> 00:13:57,967
but maybe I'm not too concerned
about what they and you want to do.

191
00:13:58,070 --> 00:14:02,370
Not every act of service is a joyride.

192
00:14:03,976 --> 00:14:06,103
Is this about, uh, what day it is?

193
00:14:06,212 --> 00:14:09,238
I know the accident
was a year ago tonight.

194
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:10,372
Maybe, I guess.

195
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:15,350
You know, this can be good for you.

196
00:14:15,454 --> 00:14:18,014
Most of the people
you're visiting tonight are shut-ins.

197
00:14:18,123 --> 00:14:20,853
You're the only person
they're going to see over the holidays.

198
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:23,258
Others, they haven't
been here for a while.

199
00:14:23,362 --> 00:14:25,660
They're not sure if the church
still cares about them.

200
00:14:25,764 --> 00:14:27,755
Yeah. We've been through this.

201
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,768
Well, let me put it in another way.

202
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:34,567
Not everything with the kids
has to be cool or hip.

203
00:14:34,673 --> 00:14:37,972
It's good for them to just do
some ministry once in a while.

204
00:14:38,077 --> 00:14:40,910
I don't... I don't know.
Man, I'm just feeling...

205
00:14:42,014 --> 00:14:45,108
I feel like I'm up against a wall
with some of these kids.

206
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:46,775
I mean, they're all great. It's just...

207
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:48,717
They haven't decided
if I'm worth listening to,

208
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:51,619
and I'm afraid this sort of thing
is gonna push them over the line,

209
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:54,056
and... and once they're on the other side,

210
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:55,990
just bury me and hire
a new seminary grad.

211
00:14:56,095 --> 00:14:58,393
At least you're overly dramatic.

212
00:14:58,497 --> 00:15:00,328
I'm sure they can identify with that.

213
00:15:00,432 --> 00:15:01,729
Okay.

214
00:15:01,834 --> 00:15:04,166
You want them to decide
you're worth listening to?

215
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:06,135
Be worth listening to.

216
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:07,728
Show them a faith

217
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:11,367
that makes you want
to do stuff like this.

218
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:15,137
See you at the services later.

219
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:16,544
All right. Later.

220
00:15:16,649 --> 00:15:19,447
Oh, and, Mitch...

221
00:15:19,551 --> 00:15:23,419
technically, old people are still people.

222
00:15:23,522 --> 00:15:24,921
I'm not sure that's true,

223
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:27,424
but I'll look it up on the Internet later.

224
00:15:27,526 --> 00:15:28,686
Yeah, do that.

225
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:06,154
Lucio Boyle?

226
00:16:06,265 --> 00:16:08,130
Don't get up.
I'm Gordon Macintosh.

227
00:16:08,233 --> 00:16:09,791
I'll be working with Samantha

228
00:16:09,902 --> 00:16:12,302
representing your ex-wife
from here on out.

229
00:16:12,404 --> 00:16:13,735
I know you two have met,

230
00:16:13,839 --> 00:16:15,739
and this is Greg, our file clerk.

231
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:18,001
Lefty.

232
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:19,509
Excuse me?

233
00:16:20,612 --> 00:16:22,512
His nickname. Cute as it is,

234
00:16:22,614 --> 00:16:24,047
we won't be using it today.

235
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,207
I'm sure you'll understand.

236
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:26,511
I'll call you back.

237
00:16:31,557 --> 00:16:33,548
Everyone calls me Lefty.

238
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:39,459
Of course they do.

239
00:16:39,565 --> 00:16:40,759
If my parents
had named me Lu...

240
00:16:40,866 --> 00:16:43,027
I'm a lefty, too. Born that way.

241
00:16:44,770 --> 00:16:48,638
Oh, in my case, it's a little weird
'cause I'm not even left-handed.

242
00:16:48,741 --> 00:16:52,040
Uh, where is your representation?

243
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:53,202
My lawyer and I,

244
00:16:53,312 --> 00:16:55,906
we don't see eye to eye
on a few things, so...

245
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:57,846
You don't have a lawyer.

246
00:16:57,950 --> 00:16:59,542
Right.

247
00:16:59,651 --> 00:17:01,881
Anyways, when I was growing up as a kid,

248
00:17:01,987 --> 00:17:03,818
we didn't have a whole lot of money,

249
00:17:03,922 --> 00:17:06,891
so every time I wanted to play ball,

250
00:17:06,992 --> 00:17:10,484
I had to borrow my brother's
left-handed baseball glove,

251
00:17:10,596 --> 00:17:13,929
and because of that
I really wasn't any good,

252
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:16,126
and all the kids that I played with,

253
00:17:16,235 --> 00:17:18,703
they didn't know I was right-handed,

254
00:17:18,804 --> 00:17:22,706
so they just thought that, uh...

255
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:25,333
well, they just thought
that I wasn't any good.

256
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:28,710
All rightie.

257
00:17:28,814 --> 00:17:31,408
Greg, we need mochas.

258
00:17:31,517 --> 00:17:32,814
Mr. Boyle,

259
00:17:32,918 --> 00:17:36,251
you realize you have a right
to have representation with you,

260
00:17:36,355 --> 00:17:40,724
and since you've chosen
not to have counsel at this hearing,

261
