00:31:44,335 --> 00:31:45,893
Two more minutes.

525
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:51,669
Mary!

526
00:31:51,976 --> 00:31:55,070
Hey. I thought
I might see you here.

527
00:31:55,179 --> 00:31:58,012
Yeah, well, he needs me
here, I think.

528
00:31:58,116 --> 00:31:59,583
Have you seen him lately?

529
00:31:59,684 --> 00:32:02,312
Uh, no, no, no, not exactly.

530
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:06,083
Uh, my schedule's pretty full now
with the high-schoolers and all.

531
00:32:06,190 --> 00:32:07,521
I do need to find time...

532
00:32:07,625 --> 00:32:08,956
He needs to see people, Mitch,

533
00:32:09,060 --> 00:32:10,084
people who love him.

534
00:32:10,194 --> 00:32:11,821
I know that sometimes it's awkward,

535
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:13,261
but it's so good for him.

536
00:32:13,364 --> 00:32:15,491
I know, Mary. You're right.

537
00:32:18,436 --> 00:32:20,131
Hey. Tough guy.

538
00:32:20,238 --> 00:32:21,671
Merry Christmas.

539
00:32:21,773 --> 00:32:22,899
Merry Christmas.

540
00:32:23,007 --> 00:32:24,440
Hey, you know what?

541
00:32:24,542 --> 00:32:26,703
I'm going to stop by your house
sometime soon, okay?

542
00:32:26,811 --> 00:32:28,278
And go to the swings park?

543
00:32:28,379 --> 00:32:29,437
Yeah. Yeah, that's right.

544
00:32:29,547 --> 00:32:31,515
- We love the swings, don't we?
- Yeah.

545
00:32:34,452 --> 00:32:36,943
I'm sorry I haven't been a good friend,

546
00:32:37,055 --> 00:32:38,750
to Rick or to you.

547
00:32:38,856 --> 00:32:41,154
I still don't know
what to do with all this.

548
00:32:41,259 --> 00:32:42,419
It's not an excuse.

549
00:32:42,527 --> 00:32:44,961
I'm just saying I'm really sorry.

550
00:32:45,063 --> 00:32:46,894
Not that I should
feel sorry for myself.

551
00:32:46,998 --> 00:32:49,694
I was back on my feet
a month after the accident.

552
00:32:49,801 --> 00:32:51,632
You're the one who got the bad deal.

553
00:32:51,736 --> 00:32:53,636
You got a bad deal, too, Mitch.

554
00:32:53,738 --> 00:32:55,296
I know how close you were.

555
00:32:55,406 --> 00:32:56,964
Yeah, but I'm not...

556
00:33:00,611 --> 00:33:02,670
You know what? I'm going to stop talking now.

557
00:33:02,780 --> 00:33:04,748
It's okay. You're right.

558
00:33:04,849 --> 00:33:06,749
I really did get screwed
on this deal, huh?

559
00:33:08,019 --> 00:33:10,146
Hey, why don't you
come to church tonight?

560
00:33:10,254 --> 00:33:11,983
We haven't seen you there
since it happened.

561
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:13,819
Tonight might be
the right night for it.

562
00:33:13,925 --> 00:33:14,949
I can't, Mitch.

563
00:33:15,059 --> 00:33:16,253
Come on.
I'll make sure no one...

564
00:33:16,361 --> 00:33:18,659
I can't. Okay? I just can't.

565
00:33:18,763 --> 00:33:21,960
Well, we all love you
there, Mary, right?

566
00:33:22,066 --> 00:33:23,226
Yeah.

567
00:33:25,536 --> 00:33:26,468
Right? Mary?

568
00:33:27,572 --> 00:33:29,802
Yeah. Right. I know.

569
00:33:31,342 --> 00:33:33,003
Does everybody still love Rick?

570
00:33:39,984 --> 00:33:41,110
I'm sorry, Mitch.

571
00:33:43,554 --> 00:33:45,681
I really am glad I saw you.

572
00:33:47,025 --> 00:33:49,152
Let's keep in touch, okay?

573
00:33:49,260 --> 00:33:51,319
And I know that tonight
might be too tough,

574
00:33:51,429 --> 00:33:53,056
but please see him.

575
00:33:53,164 --> 00:33:54,688
I know.

576
00:33:54,799 --> 00:33:56,323
Okay.

577
00:33:56,434 --> 00:33:58,231
Merry Christmas.

578
00:34:01,806 --> 00:34:03,000
Come on, honey.

579
00:34:05,410 --> 00:34:07,378
Oh, and Rick has a beard now,

580
00:34:07,478 --> 00:34:08,604
so if you kiss him,

581
00:34:08,713 --> 00:34:09,839
his beard might be tickly.

582
00:34:09,947 --> 00:34:11,505
Got it.

583
00:34:32,403 --> 00:34:34,496
You shouldn't be here, Lefty.

584
00:34:34,605 --> 00:34:37,574
Oh, hey, Gary. It's me, Lefty.

585
00:34:37,675 --> 00:34:38,767
<i>I know it's you.</i>

586
00:34:38,876 --> 00:34:41,037
<i>Why do you think I just called you Lefty?</i>

587
00:34:41,145 --> 00:34:42,703
You got to get out of here.

588
00:34:42,814 --> 00:34:45,874
<i>Can I just get the rest</i>
<i>of my stuff, please...</i>

589
00:34:47,485 --> 00:34:48,850
Gary...

590
00:34:50,421 --> 00:34:52,821
<i>You mean the rest of those paint cans?</i>

591
00:35:01,999 --> 00:35:03,523
Well, all right, then.

592
00:35:03,634 --> 00:35:06,432
<i>I'm going now...</i>

593
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:07,931
<i>Gary.</i>

594
00:35:17,615 --> 00:35:18,582
Lefty?

595
00:35:46,077 --> 00:35:48,944
Hey! Lefty, get back here!

596
00:35:55,086 --> 00:35:56,280
Lefty!

597
00:36:24,348 --> 00:36:27,181
What do you want to do?

598
00:36:27,285 --> 00:36:29,116
Fix the thing, I guess.

599
00:36:29,220 --> 00:36:31,188
Want me to call the cops?

600
00:36:31,289 --> 00:36:33,814
No. Forget it.

601
00:36:33,925 --> 00:36:35,825
I just want to be rid of him.

602
00:37:18,836 --> 00:37:19,768
What?

603
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,394
What do you mean, what?

604
00:37:21,505 --> 00:37:22,403
I got the stuff.

605
00:37:22,506 --> 00:37:24,337
Get out here and give me a hand.

606
00:37:24,442 --> 00:37:26,842
Just stop that honking.

607
00:37:26,944 --> 00:37:28,206
It's Christmas Eve.

608
00:37:28,312 --> 00:37:30,041
There's neighbors all around.

609
00:37:30,147 --> 00:37:32,274
Back that piece of junk in here.

610
00:37:39,890 --> 00:37:41,221
I'm coming out.

611
00:37:41,325 --> 00:37:43,555
Come on, hurry up!

612
00:37:43,661 --> 00:37:45,492
The whole neighborhood's watching.

613
00:37:45,596 --> 00:37:48,064
Come on! Let's do this quickly.

614
00:37:48,165 --> 00:37:51,032
Just open it up. We'll do it out here.

615
00:37:54,405 --> 00:37:55,929
Move it, Lefty!

616
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:56,938
What you got?

617
00:37:57,041 --> 00:37:57,939
Stuff.

618
00:37:58,042 --> 00:37:59,737
Let's see it.

619
00:37:59,844 --> 00:38:01,106
Okay. Fine.

620
00:38:03,047 --> 00:38:04,674
Get it into the garage.

621
00:38:12,356 --> 00:38:13,721
Come on.

622
00:38:26,270 --> 00:38:28,067
All right. That'll work.

623
00:38:36,147 --> 00:38:38,615
This sucker is hot, Lefty.

624
00:38:38,716 --> 00:38:40,240
That right?

625
00:38:40,351 --> 00:38:41,648
Scorching.

626
00:38:41,752 --> 00:38:44,152
I'm surprised you ain't blistering
just touching it.

627
00:38:44,255 --> 00:38:46,587
What's with all the dramatics?

628
00:38:46,691 --> 00:38:48,420
What, are we on TV?

629
00:38:48,526 --> 00:38:53,088
The folks it belongs to
won't be happy they see you with it.

630
00:38:53,197 --> 00:38:55,165
Those folks,
they wear badges.

631
00:38:55,266 --> 00:38:57,234
You know what I'm saying?

632
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:59,098
Where the heck did you get this?

633
00:38:59,203 --> 00:39:01,569
Well, why don't you tell me
about these tools?

634
00:39:01,672 --> 00:39:04,436
Then I'll see if I can remember
where I got the gun.

635
00:39:04,542 --> 00:39:08,205
Well, this is just a little more
than what I was looking for.

636
00:39:08,312 --> 00:39:09,836
What are you looking for?

637
00:39:11,449 --> 00:39:14,009
It's a gun.
It goes bang-bang.

638
00:39:14,118 --> 00:39:16,416
You want to be picky,
just get out of here.

639
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:17,578
I could care less.

640
00:39:17,688 --> 00:39:19,519
Got any bullets?

641
00:39:19,623 --> 00:39:21,022
Yeah.

642
00:39:23,227 --> 00:39:24,319
Now get out of here.

643
00:39:24,428 --> 00:39:25,725
One more thing.

644
00:39:25,830 --> 00:39:26,797
What's that?

645
00:39:28,866 --> 00:39:31,198
I'm real thirsty.

646
00:39:31,302 --> 00:39:33,065
Geez.

647
00:39:36,407 --> 00:39:37,874
Now go on!

648
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:41,002
Merry Christmas.

649
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:42,101
Yeah.

650
00:39:45,816 --> 00:39:47,044
I seen that!

651
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:45,374
Merry Christmas.

652
00:40:45,476 --> 00:40:47,171
Yep.

653
00:41:35,059 --> 00:41:36,856
Son of a...

654
00:42:00,718 --> 00:42:02,049
Can I help you find something?

655
00:42:02,152 --> 00:42:03,449
I'm hungry.

656
00:42:03,554 --> 00:42:05,818
You've come to the right place, then.

657
00:42:05,923 --> 00:42:08,824
You like cranberries?

658
00:42:08,926 --> 00:42:10,223
Cranberries?

659
00:42:10,327 --> 00:42:12,727
It's Christmas Eve.

660
00:42:12,830 --> 00:42:15,390
They taste different
on Christmas Eve?

661
00:42:15,499 --> 00:42:17,524
I guess not.

662
00:42:20,304 --> 00:42:21,464
You like turkey?

663
00:42:22,606 --> 00:42:27,634
Yeah, sure, if it's not made up
to look like bacon and stuff.

664
00:42:32,049 --> 00:42:34,745
Yeah. That'll do fine.

665
00:42:37,788 --> 00:42:38,686
How much?

666
00:42:38,789 --> 00:42:40,188
2.99.

667
00:42:41,659 --> 00:42:42,648
Got a bag?

668
00:42:48,899 --> 00:42:49,831
Merry Christmas.

669
00:42:49,934 --> 00:42:51,561
Yep.

670
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:56,369
Genius.

671
00:42:58,008 --> 00:43:00,806
Excuse me. Do you know
anything about cars?

672
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:02,572
Uh, I know a bit, yes.

673
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:04,204
Well, it keeps stalling out on me.

674
00:43:04,315 --> 00:43:06,647
I got to drive another three hours
to my parents' tonight.

675
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:08,081
I don't think I'm gonna make it.

676
00:43:08,185 --> 00:43:09,652
This isn't really a garage.

677
00:43:09,753 --> 00:43:11,482
Do you know of any
that are open around here?

678
00:43:11,589 --> 00:43:13,318
- I mean, it's Christmas Eve.
- I know.

679
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:14,686
And that's a problem.
Everything's closed.

680
00:43:14,792 --> 00:43:16,191
Nothing?

681
00:43:16,293 --> 00:43:18,523
I really doubt it.

682
00:43:18,629 --> 00:43:19,994
Right.

683
00:43:22,399 --> 00:43:23,491
Hi, Mom.

684
00:43:23,601 --> 00:43:25,296
No, we're still here.

685
00:43:25,402 --> 00:43:28,166
No, not home, just...

686
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:30,536
It doesn't look
like we'll be there tonight.

687
00:43:30,641 --> 00:43:32,040
Well, the car's shot,

688
00:43:32,142 --> 00:43:34,337
and I can't get anybody
to look at it right now.

689
00:43:35,779 --> 00:43:37,804
Yeah, it's... I know. It's lousy.

690
00:43:37,915 --> 00:43:39,177
I know.

691
00:43:39,283 --> 00:43:41,979
What am I supposed
to do about it?

692
00:43:42,086 --> 00:43:45,886
Mom, everything is closed.

693
00:43:45,990 --> 00:43:48,117
I can't just rent a car tonight.

694
00:43:48,225 --> 00:43:50,386
I'm going to have to see
if anybody can drive

695
00:43:50,494 --> 00:43:52,189
in the middle of nowhere
on Christmas Eve

696
00:43:52,296 --> 00:43:53,854
and give us a ride back home.

697
00:43:53,964 --> 00:43:56,023
Honey, come here.
Stay by me right now, okay?

698
00:43:56,133 --> 00:43:57,623
Mommy's on the phone
with Grandma.

699
00:43:59,036 --> 00:44:00,094
Okay. You know what?

700
00:44:00,204 --> 00:44:01,865
I'm going to call you later.

701
00:44:01,972 --> 00:44:03,303
Mom...

702
00:44:05,676 --> 00:44:08,270
Yeah, I wish Rick was here, too.

703
00:44:08,379 --> 00:44:10,006
Thanks for sharing.

704
00:44:10,114 --> 00:44:11,911
Right. Bye.

705
00:44:15,686 --> 00:44:18,246
I guess I could look at it, but l... l...

706
00:44:18,355 --> 00:44:19,447
What?

707
00:44:19,556 --> 00:44:23,549
Uh, I was just saying
that I could take a look at it, I guess.

708
00:44:23,661 --> 00:44:25,720
I mean, I don't know
a whole lot, but...

709
00:44:25,829 --> 00:44:27,194
Really? That would be great.

710
00:44:27,297 --> 00:44:29,322
Anything you could
do would be great.

711
00:44:29,433 --> 00:44:30,400
All right.

712
00:44:37,408 --> 00:44:40,969
And a Happy New Year

713
00:44:41,078 --> 00:44:42,739
Merry Christmas!

714
00:44:42,846 --> 00:44:45,246
Thank you. Thank you so much.

715
00:44:45,349 --> 00:44:48,284
Can we offer you a ride
to church tonight?

716
00:44:48,385 --> 00:44:49,909
That's very nice,

717
00:44:50,020 --> 00:44:52,545
but we need to get our sleep.

718
00:44:52,656 --> 00:44:54,419
Understood completely.

719
00:44:54,525 --> 00:44:57,494
Oh, uh, can we offer you
this small gift

720
00:44:57,594 --> 00:44:58,526
from the youth group?

721
00:44:58,629 --> 00:45:00,790
Two gifts: One for each of you.

722
00:45:00,898 --> 00:45:02,798
Well, we really don't need...

723
00:45:02,900 --> 00:45:05,027
We'd like for you to have them.

724
00:45:05,135 --> 00:45:10,163
Just a reminder you, uh, haven't been, uh,
forgotten.

725
00:45:10,274 --> 00:45:14,301
Thank you again.
Merry Christmas.

726
00:45:17,915 --> 00:45:19,348
Moving right along.

727
00:45:27,324 --> 00:45:28,382
Is that bad?

728
00:45:28,492 --> 00:45:30,460
Yeah. I think it's pretty bad.

729
00:45:30,561 --> 00:45:31,858
Can you fix it?

730
00:45:31,962 --> 00:45:33,953
If I had an air filter,

731
00:45:34,064 --> 00:45:36,191
but I don't carry
that sort of thing here.

732
00:45:36,300 --> 00:45:37,494
It's a convenience store.

733
00:45:37,601 --> 00:45:39,296
Well, that's not very
convenient, now is it?

734
00:45:39,403 --> 00:45:42,736
I've heard that one a few times.

735
00:45:42,840 --> 00:45:44,171
Sorry.

736
00:45:45,909 --> 00:45:48,173
Oh, wow.

737
00:45:48,278 --> 00:45:49,711
This is another problem.

738
00:45:49,813 --> 00:45:51,337
When was the last time
you had a tune-up?

739
00:45:51,448 --> 00:45:53,177
A what?

740
00:45:53,283 --> 00:45:56,150
Oh, uh, that would be last Christmas.

741
00:45:56,253 --> 00:45:59,154
Probably the fall before...
before that, actually.

742
00:45:59,256 --> 00:46:00,883
Rick, my husband,

743
00:46:00,991 --> 00:46:02,356
thought that a fall tune-up

744
00:46:02,459 --> 00:46:04,393
would be just fine
for Christmas travel.

745
00:46:04,495 --> 00:46:06,395
You're lucky it's running at all.

746
00:46:06,497 --> 00:46:07,862
The points are trashed.

747
00:46:07,965 --> 00:46:09,592
The filter's disgusting.

748
00:46:09,700 --> 00:46:11,998
I can't imagine what
the oil must look like.

749
00:46:12,102 --> 00:46:14,127
Last fall?

750
00:46:14,238 --> 00:46:16,206
Why didn't you bring it in after that?

751
00:46:16,306 --> 00:46:18,706
Rick always handled
things like that.

752
00:46:18,809 --> 00:46:21,505
Why did he let it go so long?

753
00:46:21,612 --> 00:46:24,274
Well, that's a loaded question.

754
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:31,751
Rick was in a car
accident last year.

755
00:46:31,855 --> 00:46:34,153
He lives in a home now.

756
00:46:34,258 --> 00:46:35,156
Sorry.

757
00:46:35,259 --> 00:46:36,248
No, it's okay.

758
00:46:36,360 --> 00:46:38,123
But it... it left him
brain damaged,

759
00:46:38,228 --> 00:46:40,253
and they're not sure what kind
of recovery he could have,

760
00:46:40,364 --> 00:46:43,265
if at all, so...

761
00:46:43,367 --> 00:46:47,633
Anyway, he hasn't been in the mood
to take the car in for a tune-up this year.

762
00:46:47,738 --> 00:46:49,171
I can tell you that.

763
00:46:53,010 --> 00:46:55,877
I suppose you'd like to make it
to your folks' place tonight, huh?

764
00:46:55,979 --> 00:46:58,277
You know what? I appreciate
you even trying. I do.

765
00:46:58,382 --> 00:47:00,907
If you help me, we could jerry-rig
the points and plugs,

766
00:47:01,018 --> 00:47:02,349
clean up the cap a bit.

767
00:47:02,452 --> 00:47:03,919
Um, we could change the oil.

768
00:47:04,021 --> 00:47:07,013
I do have oil here.
How convenient is that?

769
00:47:07,124 --> 00:47:09,183
Take the air hose. I'll blow out this filter.

770
00:47:09,293 --> 00:47:11,056
Maybe we can get by
without a new one.

771
00:47:11,161 --> 00:47:12,924
If all goes well, and that's a huge if,

772
00:47:13,030 --> 00:47:15,191
we'll have you on the road
in a couple of hours.

773
00:47:15,299 --> 00:47:17,267
I don't have to have a clue
what you said, right?

774
00:47:17,367 --> 00:47:18,356
Not if I don't.

775
00:47:19,603 --> 00:47:20,934
I'll show you what to do.

776
00:47:21,038 --> 00:47:23,734
Oh, uh, Kirk?

777
00:47:23,841 --> 00:47:24,739
Yeah.

778
00:47:24,842 --> 00:47:27,106
I'm Mary, and this is Jacob.

779
00:47:27,211 --> 00:47:29,372
Jacob. Hey, Jacob.

780
00:47:31,315 --> 00:47:33,545
Why don't you go in
and read your book?

781
00:47:47,764 --> 00:47:48,788
Yes.

782
00:47:48,899 --> 00:47:50,264
Mrs. Boyle?

783
00:47:50,367 --> 00:47:52,858
I'm Mrs. Boyle. And you are?

784
00:47:52,970 --> 00:47:54,494
My name is Margaret,

785
00:47:54,605 --> 00:47:56,470
and I'm with Meals On Wheels.

786
00:47:56,573 --> 00:48:00,236
Oh, I can't afford
to give anything this year.

787
00:48:00,344 --> 00:48:02,175
Oh, no. We're not here
to collect money.

788
00:48:02,279 --> 00:48:04,008
We're here with your Christmas dinner.

789
00:48:04,114 --> 00:48:05,604
Merry Christmas.

