01:09:30,332 --> 01:09:31,799
So then what are you doing here?

1055
01:09:33,669 --> 01:09:35,398
When I bought it, I was a genius.

1056
01:09:35,504 --> 01:09:37,563
It's... out in the middle of nowhere,

1057
01:09:37,673 --> 01:09:39,732
but the city limits
were headed this way.

1058
01:09:39,842 --> 01:09:41,139
I was... I was gonna sell it.

1059
01:09:41,243 --> 01:09:42,141
Reinvest.

1060
01:09:42,244 --> 01:09:43,734
Make a fortune.

1061
01:09:43,846 --> 01:09:46,371
But the city just never made it,
and I got stuck here.

1062
01:09:47,683 --> 01:09:49,776
Uh, so l... I figured, uh,

1063
01:09:49,885 --> 01:09:51,546
maybe I'd have a chance if I made it

1064
01:09:51,654 --> 01:09:53,554
a different kind of a gas station...

1065
01:09:53,656 --> 01:09:56,090
a destination-type place, you know?

1066
01:09:56,192 --> 01:09:57,682
Uh, gourmet coffee?

1067
01:09:57,793 --> 01:09:59,727
Good food? Great service?

1068
01:09:59,828 --> 01:10:01,921
Clean as I could get it?

1069
01:10:02,031 --> 01:10:06,593
Problem was I did all that,
and no one gave a rip.

1070
01:10:06,702 --> 01:10:08,795
So it's never gonna be
a destination for anyone.

1071
01:10:08,904 --> 01:10:10,997
It's just a stop along the way.

1072
01:10:13,209 --> 01:10:14,176
I don't know.

1073
01:10:22,718 --> 01:10:24,948
You know...

1074
01:10:25,054 --> 01:10:27,682
you think about that one thing
that you can contribute.

1075
01:10:29,058 --> 01:10:31,117
What's my thing?
That I make a good pot of coffee?

1076
01:10:31,227 --> 01:10:34,219
Most of my customers don't care
about gourmet coffee anyway.

1077
01:10:34,330 --> 01:10:35,319
They want gas

1078
01:10:35,431 --> 01:10:37,456
and a Styrofoam cup of pennies
by the register.

1079
01:10:37,566 --> 01:10:39,261
That's about it.

1080
01:11:51,140 --> 01:11:53,165
Tonight's the anniversary.

1081
01:11:55,144 --> 01:11:56,475
Of the accident?

1082
01:11:56,578 --> 01:11:57,875
Yeah.

1083
01:11:59,982 --> 01:12:01,040
Oh, wow.

1084
01:12:01,150 --> 01:12:02,777
Yeah.

1085
01:12:02,885 --> 01:12:04,876
He was a good man.

1086
01:12:04,987 --> 01:12:06,386
He is...

1087
01:12:06,488 --> 01:12:07,386
a good man,

1088
01:12:07,489 --> 01:12:09,218
but he <i>was</i> a good man.

1089
01:12:11,393 --> 01:12:12,951
I still love him so much.

1090
01:12:15,331 --> 01:12:17,231
I meant what I said.

1091
01:12:17,333 --> 01:12:19,801
You know, in my vows...
"For better or for worse."

1092
01:12:19,902 --> 01:12:21,233
All of it.

1093
01:12:21,337 --> 01:12:22,497
Yeah.

1094
01:12:28,677 --> 01:12:30,235
Are...

1095
01:12:30,346 --> 01:12:31,313
you okay?

1096
01:12:31,413 --> 01:12:32,380
Yeah.

1097
01:12:34,516 --> 01:12:35,778
I just... I haven't had a chance

1098
01:12:35,884 --> 01:12:37,511
to breathe about this for a while...

1099
01:12:37,619 --> 01:12:40,918
between fighting for him and...

1100
01:12:41,023 --> 01:12:43,583
dealing with his friends
and staying strong for Jacob.

1101
01:12:43,692 --> 01:12:44,659
I just...

1102
01:12:46,195 --> 01:12:48,493
I haven't even cried in months, so...

1103
01:13:45,921 --> 01:13:47,855
Hey, guys. Welcome back.

1104
01:13:47,956 --> 01:13:49,321
Brett. Gretchen.

1105
01:13:49,425 --> 01:13:51,222
Hey, good to see you. How'd it go.

1106
01:13:51,326 --> 01:13:52,258
Not bad.

1107
01:13:52,361 --> 01:13:53,259
- Yeah?
- It was cool.

1108
01:13:53,362 --> 01:13:55,990
Hey, everybody, head upstairs.

1109
01:13:56,098 --> 01:13:58,464
Bathroom break,
and then free time until the service.

1110
01:13:59,701 --> 01:14:00,668
So?

1111
01:14:03,439 --> 01:14:04,599
What's to say?

1112
01:14:04,706 --> 01:14:05,832
We did our duty.

1113
01:14:05,941 --> 01:14:08,409
We sang for some folks,
invited them to church.

1114
01:14:08,510 --> 01:14:10,808
But they shut their doors
and went back to their lonely lives.

1115
01:14:10,913 --> 01:14:12,210
You... handed out the packets?

1116
01:14:12,314 --> 01:14:13,246
We did.

1117
01:14:13,348 --> 01:14:15,248
That's good.

1118
01:14:15,350 --> 01:14:16,317
You know...

1119
01:14:17,953 --> 01:14:20,080
I'm still not sure
what value all this had.

1120
01:14:22,791 --> 01:14:23,883
Maybe you never will.

1121
01:14:23,992 --> 01:14:25,983
So, what's the point, then?

1122
01:14:26,094 --> 01:14:27,652
None of them are gonna be coming

1123
01:14:27,763 --> 01:14:29,162
to church tonight because of our visit.

1124
01:14:29,264 --> 01:14:30,663
They... They didn't care.

1125
01:14:30,766 --> 01:14:32,700
And the kids sure aren't gonna
get anything out of it.

1126
01:14:32,801 --> 01:14:34,359
- I mean... I just...
- You know something, Mitch?

1127
01:14:34,470 --> 01:14:36,961
You go out and serve God
with that attitude,

1128
01:14:37,072 --> 01:14:40,337
there's a good chance
that nothing will come of it.

1129
01:14:41,643 --> 01:14:44,077
Maybe this is a test for you. I don't know.

1130
01:14:44,179 --> 01:14:49,242
Sometimes you do the right thing
because it's the right thing?

1131
01:14:49,351 --> 01:14:51,046
Geez, you sound like
a pastor or something.

1132
01:14:51,153 --> 01:14:53,883
And, look, you don't know
what's gonna come of tonight.

1133
01:14:53,989 --> 01:14:55,786
I got it. I got it.

1134
01:14:56,825 --> 01:14:58,656
It's just tonight...

1135
01:14:58,760 --> 01:14:59,954
of all nights.

1136
01:15:00,062 --> 01:15:01,222
You know?

1137
01:15:01,330 --> 01:15:02,297
I mean...

1138
01:15:02,397 --> 01:15:04,058
before, a year ago,
when Rick was here,

1139
01:15:04,166 --> 01:15:05,064
he mattered.

1140
01:15:05,167 --> 01:15:06,498
He was important.

1141
01:15:06,602 --> 01:15:08,536
He had good ideas.
The kids thought he was exciting.

1142
01:15:08,637 --> 01:15:10,468
And now it's a year later,
and we've got him

1143
01:15:10,572 --> 01:15:12,403
tooling around, singing on porches.

1144
01:15:12,508 --> 01:15:13,805
Badly, I might add.

1145
01:15:13,909 --> 01:15:15,843
I hear you, Mitch.

1146
01:15:15,944 --> 01:15:17,172
I do.

1147
01:15:18,680 --> 01:15:21,080
I want to talk to you about this, okay?

1148
01:15:21,183 --> 01:15:23,014
Can we talk after the service?

1149
01:15:23,118 --> 01:15:24,016
Yeah.

1150
01:15:24,119 --> 01:15:25,814
Great. Thank you.

1151
01:15:30,025 --> 01:15:31,583
You know...

1152
01:15:31,693 --> 01:15:33,251
there was something tonight...

1153
01:15:33,362 --> 01:15:34,488
kinda odd.

1154
01:15:34,596 --> 01:15:36,587
Um...

1155
01:15:36,698 --> 01:15:38,256
Eva Boyle.

1156
01:15:38,367 --> 01:15:40,096
Is she a little off?

1157
01:15:40,202 --> 01:15:41,499
Something didn't seem quite right,

1158
01:15:41,603 --> 01:15:43,264
and... and I don't know what it was.

1159
01:15:43,372 --> 01:15:44,532
Yeah, Eva Boyle.

1160
01:15:44,640 --> 01:15:45,834
I, uh...

1161
01:15:45,941 --> 01:15:49,877
She's kept a lot of our church ladies
on their knees for a long time now.

1162
01:15:49,978 --> 01:15:51,946
Her husband's been dead ten years.

1163
01:15:52,047 --> 01:15:53,105
He was terrible.

1164
01:15:53,215 --> 01:15:55,046
Her family's scattered all over.

1165
01:15:55,150 --> 01:15:56,777
Some of them she hasn't seen for years,

1166
01:15:56,885 --> 01:16:00,616
and from what I hear,
that isn't necessarily a bad thing.

1167
01:16:01,790 --> 01:16:03,121
You sure about that?

1168
01:16:03,225 --> 01:16:04,954
She said they were all
coming to see her tomorrow.

1169
01:16:05,060 --> 01:16:06,789
No. Not likely.

1170
01:16:06,895 --> 01:16:08,055
That's great.

1171
01:16:08,163 --> 01:16:09,460
I'm glad I followed my instincts.

1172
01:16:11,967 --> 01:16:13,127
Listen.

1173
01:16:13,235 --> 01:16:15,328
Why don't you follow up
with her sometime?

1174
01:16:15,437 --> 01:16:16,836
I can go with you.

1175
01:16:18,740 --> 01:16:21,732
Mitch, I know you didn't want to,

1176
01:16:23,412 --> 01:16:25,642
but you did the right thing tonight.

1177
01:16:25,747 --> 01:16:27,874
It was good for the kids, too.

1178
01:16:28,917 --> 01:16:29,884
Yeah.

1179
01:16:40,929 --> 01:16:44,330
<i>Long lay the world</i>

1180
01:16:44,433 --> 01:16:48,893
<i>In sin and error pining</i>

1181
01:16:49,004 --> 01:16:51,495
<i>Till he appeared</i>

1182
01:16:51,607 --> 01:16:55,805
<i>And the soul felt its worth</i>

1183
01:16:57,512 --> 01:17:00,970
<i>A thrill of hope</i>

1184
01:17:01,083 --> 01:17:05,383
<i>The weary world rejoices</i>

1185
01:20:29,558 --> 01:20:30,525
Hello?

1186
01:20:38,166 --> 01:20:39,827
What are you doing here?

1187
01:20:40,869 --> 01:20:42,837
- It's me.
- I know who it is.

1188
01:20:44,172 --> 01:20:46,231
Why didn't you answer the door?

1189
01:20:49,845 --> 01:20:51,972
Because I didn't want
to be bothered.

1190
01:20:55,617 --> 01:20:56,549
Right. I'll just, uh...

1191
01:20:56,651 --> 01:20:59,142
No. What... What
are you doing here?

1192
01:21:01,022 --> 01:21:03,991
I came by to, um, just get something.

1193
01:21:07,195 --> 01:21:08,162
Well...

1194
01:21:09,965 --> 01:21:10,989
Give me your jacket.

1195
01:21:11,099 --> 01:21:13,693
I'll keep it on. I'm not staying.

1196
01:21:17,038 --> 01:21:18,130
How's Heather?

1197
01:21:20,041 --> 01:21:22,339
She ran out on me two years ago, Ma.

1198
01:21:24,880 --> 01:21:26,973
Well, how would I know that?

1199
01:21:30,051 --> 01:21:31,018
Right.

1200
01:21:33,555 --> 01:21:36,183
Life doesn't always turn out
as we hoped, does it?

1201
01:21:37,893 --> 01:21:39,793
You have no idea.

1202
01:21:39,895 --> 01:21:41,362
The hell I don't.

1203
01:21:48,570 --> 01:21:50,037
The kids. They okay?

1204
01:21:51,573 --> 01:21:53,200
Heather won't let me see 'em.

1205
01:21:54,242 --> 01:21:55,800
Now what have you done?

1206
01:21:55,911 --> 01:21:57,003
Ma.

1207
01:21:59,247 --> 01:22:00,305
All right.

1208
01:22:02,417 --> 01:22:03,782
What do you want?

1209
01:22:06,922 --> 01:22:10,653
Lucio, l... You... You scared me half to death.

1210
01:22:10,759 --> 01:22:13,990
Lefty, Ma.
Lefty.

1211
01:22:14,095 --> 01:22:15,027
Oh, for heaven's sakes.

1212
01:22:15,130 --> 01:22:16,825
You're not even left-handed.

1213
01:22:22,437 --> 01:22:23,734
All right, Lefty.

1214
01:22:25,106 --> 01:22:26,664
You came here...

1215
01:22:26,775 --> 01:22:28,675
to this house...

1216
01:22:28,777 --> 01:22:30,608
on this night...

1217
01:22:30,712 --> 01:22:32,475
- for no reason?
- I got a reason.

1218
01:22:32,580 --> 01:22:33,740
Well, what is it?

1219
01:22:41,289 --> 01:22:42,722
I came to wish you a Merry Christmas.

1220
01:22:44,793 --> 01:22:46,420
Actually, that ain't right.

1221
01:22:46,528 --> 01:22:47,586
I came here...

1222
01:22:49,030 --> 01:22:52,761
so you could...
wish me a Merry Christmas.

1223
01:22:57,305 --> 01:23:00,206
You... You need me to wish you
a Merry Christmas?

1224
01:23:04,145 --> 01:23:06,204
Well, why would you...

1225
01:23:06,314 --> 01:23:07,212
Why...

1226
01:23:07,315 --> 01:23:08,748
'Cause you're my ma.

1227
01:23:09,985 --> 01:23:11,077
That's all.

1228
01:23:17,492 --> 01:23:18,789
Well, Merry Christmas.

1229
01:23:26,001 --> 01:23:27,025
Okay.

1230
01:23:31,506 --> 01:23:32,734
I'll just be going.

1231
01:23:32,841 --> 01:23:33,739
No. No, no. Wait.

1232
01:23:33,842 --> 01:23:35,036
Please. L... I'm sorry.

1233
01:23:35,143 --> 01:23:37,441
Um... it's just...

1234
01:23:38,513 --> 01:23:40,003
all so unexpected.

1235
01:23:41,049 --> 01:23:41,947
Yeah, I know.

1236
01:23:42,050 --> 01:23:43,847
Uh, let me make you some tea.

1237
01:23:43,952 --> 01:23:45,715
Uh, are you hungry at all?

1238
01:23:45,820 --> 01:23:47,014
L... I've got leftovers.

1239
01:23:47,122 --> 01:23:48,487
- Ma...
- No, please.

1240
01:23:48,590 --> 01:23:51,115
Come on. It'll just take a minute.

1241
01:24:20,221 --> 01:24:22,280
I gotta say...
you're the best thing

1242
01:24:22,390 --> 01:24:24,449
that's happened to me all evening.

1243
01:24:24,559 --> 01:24:25,856
That right?

1244
01:24:26,895 --> 01:24:31,195
You ever hear a group of teenagers
sing "Silent Night"?

1245
01:24:32,233 --> 01:24:33,962
Not silent enough, huh?

1246
01:24:34,069 --> 01:24:35,730
Definitely not.

1247
01:24:38,073 --> 01:24:39,904
- Lucio, no! Oh!
- What? Ma.

1248
01:24:41,409 --> 01:24:43,570
Oh, you didn't drink
any of that, did you?

1249
01:24:43,678 --> 01:24:44,576
No, Ma.

1250
01:24:44,679 --> 01:24:46,442
Oh... I'm sorry.

1251
01:24:46,548 --> 01:24:47,640
I've got a cold.

1252
01:24:47,749 --> 01:24:49,114
I just don't want you to get sick.

1253
01:24:49,217 --> 01:24:51,048
I'm so sorry. I'm sorry.

1254
01:25:02,263 --> 01:25:03,491
Ma...

1255
01:25:03,598 --> 01:25:04,656
you all right?

1256
01:25:04,766 --> 01:25:05,994
I'm fine.

1257
01:25:09,771 --> 01:25:11,830
It's Christmas Eve.
Are you going to church?

1258
01:25:11,940 --> 01:25:15,842
Oh, those Christmas carolers
asked me that this evening.

1259
01:25:15,944 --> 01:25:18,640
I told 'em I didn't think
I was gonna make it there this year.

1260
01:25:18,746 --> 01:25:19,713
How come?

1261
01:25:20,748 --> 01:25:23,410
Well... I don't have a car anymore.

1262
01:25:25,120 --> 01:25:26,314
What about the bus?

1263
01:25:27,489 --> 01:25:29,354
They changed the route last year,

1264
01:25:29,457 --> 01:25:31,118
and now the closest stop
is all the way

1265
01:25:31,226 --> 01:25:32,853
on the other side of the four-lane.

1266
01:25:33,962 --> 01:25:35,429
Oh. Here. Sit down!

1267
01:25:35,530 --> 01:25:37,259
Come on. It's just gonna be ready in a minute.

1268
01:25:37,365 --> 01:25:38,559
Get you a napkin. Get all ready.

1269
01:25:38,666 --> 01:25:40,258
It's just gonna be a minute.

1270
01:26:03,491 --> 01:26:04,924
- Hey.
- Hi.

1271
01:26:06,327 --> 01:26:08,056
So, tell me.

1272
01:26:08,163 --> 01:26:09,425
What were you gonna do
with your fortune?

1273
01:26:11,332 --> 01:26:12,560
I don't know.

1274
01:26:12,667 --> 01:26:14,066
I didn't get that far.

1275
01:26:14,169 --> 01:26:15,568
Does it really matter?

1276
01:26:15,670 --> 01:26:17,638
That's the second time
you've said that.

1277
01:26:17,739 --> 01:26:21,072
I, for one, am glad
you didn't sell this place and move on,

1278
01:26:21,176 --> 01:26:23,736
'cause I'd be stuck out here
in the middle of nowhere tonight

1279
01:26:23,845 --> 01:26:25,813
trying to get a new AAA account.

1280
01:26:26,848 --> 01:26:27,906
Yeah, that's true.

1281
01:26:28,016 --> 01:26:29,210
See?

1282
01:26:29,317 --> 01:26:31,308
It was all worth it.

1283
01:26:31,419 --> 01:26:33,910
Thanks.
That changes everything.

1284
01:26:34,022 --> 01:26:36,013
Oh, anyway,

1285
01:26:36,124 --> 01:26:37,751
it was... it was good
to talk about it.

1286
01:26:37,859 --> 01:26:39,258
So thanks.

1287
01:26:39,360 --> 01:26:40,452
Yeah.

1288
01:26:42,363 --> 01:26:44,695
Why don't you hang
out with Jacob, okay?

1289
01:26:44,799 --> 01:26:46,994
I should be able to knock
the rest out myself, okay?

1290
01:26:54,008 --> 01:26:57,375
Your brother just won't have anything
to do with me anymore.

1291
01:26:58,580 --> 01:27:01,105
Think he blames me for your father.

1292
01:27:01,216 --> 01:27:03,446
Kevin's too good for all of us now.

1293
01:27:03,551 --> 01:27:06,179
I wouldn't waste my time waiting on him.

1294
01:27:08,323 --> 01:27:10,450
You hear anything from your sister?

1295
01:27:10,558 --> 01:27:11,525
Nope.

1296
01:27:12,560 --> 01:27:13,527
Me, neither.

1297
01:27:14,562 --> 01:27:15,756
Three years.

1298
01:27:17,899 --> 01:27:21,062
Last I heard,
she was still... dancing.

1299
01:27:22,103 --> 01:27:23,161
The kids used to write me,

1300
01:27:23,271 --> 01:27:25,637
but now I don't know what's going on.

1301
01:27:25,740 --> 01:27:26,798
Is that right?

1302
01:27:29,310 --> 01:27:31,471
That girl's had a death wish since junior high.

1303
01:27:31,579 --> 01:27:33,911
I don't know how she made it as far as she did.

1304
01:27:34,015 --> 01:27:36,313
Well, it wasn't really that far.

1305
01:27:40,255 --> 01:27:42,223
I'm sorry about you and Heather.

1306
01:27:45,927 --> 01:27:48,487
I wasn't exactly Man of the Year.

1307
01:27:48,596 --> 01:27:51,565
Well, just don't you lose touch with those kids.

1308
01:27:51,666 --> 01:27:54,226
It's no fun when your kids stop talking to you.

1309
01:27:54,335 --> 01:27:56,064
Okay, Ma. I get it.

1310
01:27:57,171 --> 01:27:58,069
I'm just saying.

1311
01:27:58,172 --> 01:27:59,070
I get it.

1312
01:27:59,173 --> 01:28:00,162
All right.

1313
01:28:00,275 --> 01:28:01,333
I get it.

1314
01:28:08,449 --> 01:28:11,350
Your cousin Jeff just had another baby.

1315
01:28:11,452 --> 01:28:12,350
